Package ch.zh.transferclient.gui

Provides classes for the graphical user interface.
Version:
2.4
Author:
Daniel Bierer (Statistisches Amt des Kantons ZÃ¼rich)
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DialogDir
    This class is used to show a dialog which informs the user that a result folder has to be chosen before the the transfer-client can be activated.
    DialogFileProcessingError
    This class is used to show a dialog which informs the user that a error occurred while a file has been processed.
    DialogReceiptNotWellFormed
    This class is used to show a dialog which informs the user that a received sedex receipt file is not well formed.
    DialogSupport
    This class is used to show a dialog which informs the user about the contact details for support.
    DialogWaitingForDeactivation
    This class is used to show a dialog which informs the user that the transfer-client will be deactivated.
    EventHandlerActionListener
    This class is used to handle menu events.
    EventHandlerComponentListener
    This class is used to guarantee that components (windows) remain well arranged when components (windows) are moved.
    EventHandlerItemListener
    This class is used to handle change events of the autoactivation combobox.
    EventHandlerWindowListener
    This class is used to handle the window closing event.
    FactoryComboBoxes
    This class is used to produce combo boxes.
    FactoryTableProtocol_Detail
    This class is used to produce a protocol table.
    FactoryTableProtocol_Overview
    This class is used to produce a protocol table.
    Gui
    This class is used to produce a graphical user interface.
    GuiStart
    This class is used to show an initial frame, informing that the transfer-client is starting up.
    GuiStartupError
    This class is used to show errors which occur at startup time.
    TableCellRendererComboBox
    This class is used to produce a TableCellRendererComboBox.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    GuiStart.StatusField
    Status fields of the GuiStart that can be used for informing the end user about the current status.
